NetNumber.name: NetNumber
NetNumber.description: IPX network number. It is a 32-bit value divided into 4 octets.

HostAddress.name: HostAddress
HostAddress.description: IPX host MAC address. It is a group of the 6 octets from the MAC address.

alaIpxStaticRouteTable.name: alaIpxStaticRouteTable
alaIpxStaticRouteTable.description: The Static Routes table is used and add entries and extract information from the static routes configured in the system.

alaIpxStaticRouteEntry.name: alaIpxStaticRouteEntry
alaIpxStaticRouteEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one static route.

alaIpxStaticRouteNetNum.name: alaIpxStaticRouteNetNum
alaIpxStaticRouteNetNum.description: The IPX network number of the route's destination.

alaIpxStaticRouteNextHopNet.name: alaIpxStaticRouteNextHopNet
alaIpxStaticRouteNextHopNet.description: The IPX network number of the router used to reach the first hop in the static route.

alaIpxStaticRouteNextHopNode.name: alaIpxStaticRouteNextHopNode
alaIpxStaticRouteNextHopNode.description: The IPX node number of the router used to reach the first hop in the static route.

alaIpxStaticRouteTicks.name: alaIpxStaticRouteTicks
alaIpxStaticRouteTicks.description: The delay, in ticks, to reach the route's destination.

alaIpxStaticRouteHopCount.name: alaIpxStaticRouteHopCount
alaIpxStaticRouteHopCount.description: The number of hops necessary to reach the destination.

alaIpxStaticRouteRowStatus.name: alaIpxStaticRouteRowStatus
alaIpxStaticRouteRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. The RowStatus of a currenty active row in the alaIpxStaticRouteTable is constrained by the operational state of the corresponding static route. The RowStatus values that are supported are the following: active: This indicates that the row is active and valid. createAndGo: This will create the row and activate it. destroy: This value will deactivate the row and delete from the system.

alaIpxDefRouteTable.name: alaIpxDefRouteTable
alaIpxDefRouteTable.description: The default route table contains information about the destinations to which all packets are sent when the destination network is not known.

alaIpxDefRouteEntry.name: alaIpxDefRouteEntry
alaIpxDefRouteEntry.description: One table entry per switch for default route.

alaIpxDefRouteVlanId.name: alaIpxDefRouteVlanId
alaIpxDefRouteVlanId.description: The VlanId for this filter. If VlanId equals 0, the filter is applied globally.

alaIpxDefRouteNet.name: alaIpxDefRouteNet
alaIpxDefRouteNet.description: The IPX network number of the router used to reach the first hop in the default route.

alaIpxDefRouteNode.name: alaIpxDefRouteNode
alaIpxDefRouteNode.description: The IPX node number of the router used to reach the first hop in the default route.

alaIpxDefRouteRowStatus.name: alaIpxDefRouteRowStatus
alaIpxDefRouteRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. The RowStatus of a currenty active row in the alaIpxDefRouteTable is constrained by the operational state of the corresponding default route entry. The RowStatus values that are supported are the following: active: This indicates that the row is active and valid. createAndGo: This will create the row and activate it. destroy: This value will deactivate the row and delete from the system.

alaIpxExtMsgTable.name: alaIpxExtMsgTable
alaIpxExtMsgTable.description: The extended RIP and SAP messages table contains information about which vlans use extended RIP and SAP packets.

alaIpxExtMsgVlanId.name: alaIpxExtMsgVlanId
alaIpxExtMsgVlanId.description: The VlanId for this filter. If VlanId equals 0, the filter is applied globally.

alaIpxExtMsgMode.name: alaIpxExtMsgMode
alaIpxExtMsgMode.description: Indicates whether extended RIP/SAP packets are sent and received.

alaIpxExtMsgRowStatus.name: alaIpxExtMsgRowStatus
alaIpxExtMsgRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. The RowStatus of a currenty active row in the alaIpxExtMsgTable is constrained by the operational state of the corresponding watchdog entry. The RowStatus values that are supported are the following: active: This indicates that the row is active and valid. createAndGo: This will create the row and activate it. destroy: This value will deactivate the row and delete from the system.

alaIpxFlush.name: alaIpxFlush
alaIpxFlush.description: Flushes the routing and the SAP tables. The tables will then be rebuilt from the broadcast messages received from the networks. Reading this variable is undefined

alaIpxRipSapFilterTable.name: alaIpxRipSapFilterTable
alaIpxRipSapFilterTable.description: The IPX Rip/Sap Filter Table contains information about all filters that have been defined.

alaIpxRipSapFilterEntry.name: alaIpxRipSapFilterEntry
alaIpxRipSapFilterEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one filter.

alaIpxRipSapFilterVlanId.name: alaIpxRipSapFilterVlanId
alaIpxRipSapFilterVlanId.description: The VlanId for this filter. If VlanId equals 0, the filter is applied globally.

alaIpxRipSapFilterNet.name: alaIpxRipSapFilterNet
alaIpxRipSapFilterNet.description: The IPX Network Address to filter. A network address of all 0 's is used to denote All Networks.

alaIpxRipSapFilterNetMask.name: alaIpxRipSapFilterNetMask
alaIpxRipSapFilterNetMask.description: The IPX Network Mask to be used.

alaIpxRipSapFilterNode.name: alaIpxRipSapFilterNode
alaIpxRipSapFilterNode.description: The IPX node address to filter. A node address of all 0 's is used to denote All Nodes.

alaIpxRipSapFilterNodeMask.name: alaIpxRipSapFilterNodeMask
alaIpxRipSapFilterNodeMask.description: The IPX node address mask to be used.

alaIpxRipSapFilterSvcType.name: alaIpxRipSapFilterSvcType
alaIpxRipSapFilterSvcType.description: The SAP service type on which to filter. The SAP service types are defined by Novell.A value of ALL(65535) indicates that all services will be filtered.

alaIpxRipSapFilterMode.name: alaIpxRipSapFilterMode
alaIpxRipSapFilterMode.description: The action defined by this filter. block (1) means packets matching this filter will be blocked, and allow(0) means that packets matching this filter will be allowed.

alaIpxRipSapFilterRowStatus.name: alaIpxRipSapFilterRowStatus
alaIpxRipSapFilterRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. The RowStatus of a currenty active row in the alaIpxRipSapFilterTable is constrained by the operational state of the corresponding filter entry. The RowStatus values that are supported are the following: active: This indicates that the row is active and valid. createAndGo: This will create the row and activate it. destroy: This value will deactivate the row and delete from the system.

alaIpxWatchdogSpoofTable.name: alaIpxWatchdogSpoofTable
alaIpxWatchdogSpoofTable.description: The IPX Watchdog Spoofing Table contains information about all of the current IPX WAN watchdog spoofing entry statuses.

alaIpxWatchdogSpoofEntry.name: alaIpxWatchdogSpoofEntry
alaIpxWatchdogSpoofEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one WAN routing service.

alaIpxWatchdogSpoofVlanId.name: alaIpxWatchdogSpoofVlanId
alaIpxWatchdogSpoofVlanId.description: The VlanId of the WAN routing service that this entry applies to. If VlanId equals 0, the filter is applied globally to all WAN Vlans.

alaIpxWatchdogSpoofMode.name: alaIpxWatchdogSpoofMode
alaIpxWatchdogSpoofMode.description: This controls whether the IPX Watchdog Spoofing is enabled or disabled.When enabled, this routing service will spoof IPX Watchdog packets.When disabled, this routing service will not spoof IPX Watchdog packets.

alaIpxWatchdogSpoofRowStatus.name: alaIpxWatchdogSpoofRowStatus
alaIpxWatchdogSpoofRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. The RowStatus of a currenty active row in the alaIpxWatchdogSpoofTable is constrained by the operational state of the corresponding watchdog entry. The RowStatus values that are supported are the following: active: This indicates that the row is active and valid. createAndGo: This will create the row and activate it. destroy: This value will deactivate the row and delete from the system.

alaIpxSerialFilterTable.name: alaIpxSerialFilterTable
alaIpxSerialFilterTable.description: The IPX Serialization Filtering Table contains information about all of the current IPX WAN serialization filtering entry statuses.

alaIpxSerialFilterEntry.name: alaIpxSerialFilterEntry
alaIpxSerialFilterEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one WAN routing service.

alaIpxSerialFilterMode.name: alaIpxSerialFilterMode
alaIpxSerialFilterMode.description: This controls whether the IPX Serialization Filtering is enabled or disabled.When enabled, this routing service will filter IPX Serialization packets.When disabled, this routing service will not filter IPX Serialization packets.

alaIpxSerialFilterRowStatus.name: alaIpxSerialFilterRowStatus

The RowStatus of a currenty active row in the alaIpxSerialFilterTable is constrained by the operational state of the corresponding filter entry. The RowStatus values that are supported are the following: active: This indicates that the row is active and valid. createAndGo: This will create the row and activate it. destroy: This value will deactivate the row and delete from the system.

alaSpxKeepaliveSpoofTable.name: alaSpxKeepaliveSpoofTable
alaSpxKeepaliveSpoofTable.description: The SPX Keepalive Spoofing Table contains information about all of the current IPX WAN SPX spoofing filtering entry statuses.

alaSpxKeepaliveSpoofEntry.name: alaSpxKeepaliveSpoofEntry
alaSpxKeepaliveSpoofEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one WAN routing service.

alaSpxKeepaliveSpoofMode.name: alaSpxKeepaliveSpoofMode

alaIpxType20Table.name: alaIpxType20Table
alaIpxType20Table.description: The IPX Type 20 Table contains information about all of the current Type 20 filtering entry statuses.

alaIpxType20Entry.name: alaIpxType20Entry
alaIpxType20Entry.description: Each entry corresponds to one Virtual LAN.

alaIpxType20VlanId.name: alaIpxType20VlanId
alaIpxType20VlanId.description: The VLAN Id of the routing interface that this entry applies to. If VlanId equals 0, the filter is applied globally.

alaIpxType20Mode.name: alaIpxType20Mode
alaIpxType20Mode.description: This controls whether IPX Type 20 packet are enabled or disabled.When enabled, this routing interface will forward Type 20 packets.When disabled, the packets will not.

alaIpxType20RowStatus.name: alaIpxType20RowStatus
alaIpxType20RowStatus.description: The row status variable, used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. The RowStatus of a currenty active row in the alaIpxType20Table is constrained by the operational state of the corresponding type 20 entry. The RowStatus values that are supported are the following: active: This indicates that the row is active and valid. createAndGo: This will create the row and activate it. destroy: This value will deactivate the row and delete from the system.

alaIpxTimerTable.name: alaIpxTimerTable
alaIpxTimerTable.description: The IPX Timer Table contains information about all of the current Timer adjustments entry statuses.

alaIpxTimerEntry.name: alaIpxTimerEntry
alaIpxTimerEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one Virtual LAN.

alaIpxTimerVlanId.name: alaIpxTimerVlanId
alaIpxTimerVlanId.description: The VLAN Id of the routing interface that this entry applies to. If VlanId equals 0, the filter is applied globally.

alaIpxTimerSap.name: alaIpxTimerSap
alaIpxTimerSap.description: This controls whether IPX SAP packet timer duration.

alaIpxTimerRip.name: alaIpxTimerRip
alaIpxTimerRip.description: This controls whether IPX RIP packet timer duration.
